<paragraph id="9E4736DA9279FFF2FF6FFEE0FF0011DF" blockId="15.[178,1085,335,386]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Etymology: The specific epithet (adjective) alludes to the five impressions on the pronotum.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6E265519279FFEDFF6FFE3EFD25143C" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="117" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" type="description">
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9279FFEDFF6FFE3EFCC911E3" blockId="15.[178,1086,401,511]" lastBlockId="16.[178,1085,219,446]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="117" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Description: Large species, body length 
<quantity id="59009B3F9279FFF2FD66FE3DFD1211FA" box="[699,782,402,423]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="8.3">8.3 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="59009B3F9279FFF2FC3AFE3DFA2611FA" box="[999,1082,402,423]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9279FFF2FE92FE00FF831199" box="[335,415,431,453]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body blackish, with the posterior margins of the abdominal segments dark-reddish; legs blackish-brown with black femora and reddishbrown protarsi; antennae blackish-brown with antennomere II and base of III reddish-brown. Head (
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9266FFEDFF2BFF74FF5C10AC" box="[246,320,219,241]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse, approximately 1.3 times as wide as long, posteriorly vertically sloping ventrad towards neck, but not angulate (lateral view); behind eyes smoothly curved towards neck (dorsal view), posterior angles completely obsolete; neck approximately 0.3 times as wide as head; punctation fine and rather sparse, absent in antero-median dorsal portion and on frons; microsculpture in median dorsal portion obsolete, very shallow in lateral portion (near eyes). Eyes large, strongly bulging, and of oblong ellipsoid shape, not situated laterally, but dorso-laterally. Antenna not distinctly asymmetric, approximately 
<quantity id="59009B3F9266FFEDFE10FE07FC0611E0" box="[461,538,424,446]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long, and slender.
</paragraph>
<caption id="CA8766529279FFF2FF6FF9BEFA211660" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" startId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" targetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9279FFF2FF6FF9BEFA211660" blockId="15.[178,1085,1553,1598]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FF6FF9BEFF0A167B" bold="true" box="[178,278,1553,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Figs 28-33</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599279FFF2FEF9F9BEFC05167B" authority="Assing, 2015" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[292,537,1553,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multimpressus" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FEF9F9BEFC05167B" box="[292,537,1553,1574]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Orphnebius multimpressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B7BF57B39279FFF2FDFDF9BEFC7A167B" box="[544,614,1553,1574]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: habitus (
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FD62F9BEFCCA167B" bold="true" box="[703,726,1553,1574]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">28</emphasis>
); forebody (
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FC96F9BEFD7E167B" bold="true" box="[843,866,1553,1574]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">29</emphasis>
); abdomen (
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FC05F9BEFDF3167B" bold="true" box="[984,1007,1553,1574]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">30</emphasis>
); tergite VIII (
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FF39F987FEE61660" bold="true" box="[228,250,1576,1597]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">31</emphasis>
); sternite VIII (
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FE58F987FF871660" bold="true" box="[389,411,1576,1597]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">32</emphasis>
); spermatheca (
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89279FFF2FDF5F987FC221660" bold="true" box="[552,574,1576,1597]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">33</emphasis>
). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9266FFEDFF6FFE62FF821228" blockId="16.[178,1085,461,629]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9266FFEDFEF4FE62FF6B11BE" box="[297,375,461,483]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) moderately convex in cross-section, of transversely quadrangular shape, approximately 1.3 times as wide as long and as wide as head; anterior and posterior angles marked; disc posteriorly with five impressions together somewhat resembling a maple leaf; punctation sparse and extremely fine, barely noticeable; pubescence short and depressed; laterally, anteriorly, and posteriorly distinctly margined and without long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9266FFEDFF6FFD2AFDE912AF" blockId="16.[178,1085,645,754]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9266FFEDFEDFFD2AFF5312C6" box="[258,335,645,667]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) distinctly widened posteriorly and nearly as long as pronotum; suture gaping posteriorly; punctation moderately sparse and distinctly granulose; interstices with pronounced microreticulation. Hind wings present. Legs conspicuously long and slender; mesotiba weakly, metatibia more strongly curved; metatibia 
<quantity id="59009B3F9266FFEDFCB3FD72FDA712AF" box="[878,955,733,754]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9266FFEDFF6FFCADFD801442" blockId="16.[178,1086,770,1055]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9266FFEDFEF8FCADFF731345" box="[293,367,770,792]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) wedge-shaped, distinctly tapering posteriad (lateral sternal processes not considered); sternites III-VI postero-laterally with conspicuous processes, that of sternite IV and particularly that of sternite V enormous and of highly characteristic shape; tergites strongly transverse, disc of tergite V 1.8 times as broad as long (length measured from anterior transverse line to posterior margin; width measured between paratergites); tergites III-VI impunctate, except for some barely noticeable minute setiferous punctures at the posterior margins; integument without microsculpture; posterior 3/5 of tergite VII and tergite VIII with coarse and dense non-setiferous punctures; posterior margin of tergite VII with distinct palisade fringe; sternite VIII posteriorly with pair of lateral processes and pronounced median process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9266FFEDFF6FFB9BFD25143C" blockId="16.[178,1085,1070,1122]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<specimenCount id="88FEFD539266FFEDFF6FFB9BFEDB1414" box="[178,199,1076,1097]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: tergite VIII posteriorly with numerous denticles (
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9266FFEDFD12FB81FD001418" box="[719,796,1070,1093]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9266FFEDFC30FB81FA251419" box="[1005,1081,1070,1092]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
; spermatheca small in relation to body size, shaped as in 
<figureCitation id="06C32A5F9266FFEDFD36FBE3FD25143C" box="[747,825,1100,1122]" captionStart="Figs 28-33" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[182,1082,519,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-136@15.[178,1082,519,1543]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 28-33: Orphnebius multimpressus nov.sp.: habitus (28); forebody (29); abdomen (30); tergite VIII (31); sternite VIII (32); spermatheca (33). Scale bars: 28-30: 1.0 mm; 31-32: 0.5 mm; 33: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413952/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 33.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6E265519266FFECFF6FFBDEFCDA113B" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="118" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9266FFECFF6FFBDEFCDA113B" blockId="16.[178,1085,1136,1598]" lastBlockId="17.[178,1085,219,358]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="118" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Comparative notes: According to 
<bibRefCitation id="FA694B2B9266FFEDFD42FBDEFD9A14DA" author="HLAVAC P &amp; NEWTON A" box="[671,902,1136,1159]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref13311" refString="HLAVAC P., NEWTON A. F. &amp; M. MARUYAMA (2011): World catalogue of the species of the tribe Lomechusini (Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Zootaxa 3075: 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="2011">HLAVÁČ et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, 13 species have been assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFEBEFB21FFCF14FE" box="[355,467,1166,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deroleptus">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFEBEFB21FFCF14FE" box="[355,467,1166,1187]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Deroleptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, most of them distributed in the Oriental region (
<collectingCountry id="E6EF764A9266FFEDFC0CFB21FA2514F9" box="[977,1081,1166,1188]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="E6EF764A9266FFEDFEFBFB03FF99149F" box="[294,389,1196,1218]" name="Malaysia" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E6EF764A9266FFEDFE4EFB03FFE4149F" box="[403,504,1196,1218]" name="Indonesia" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E6EF764A9266FFEDFDD8FB03FC60149F" box="[517,636,1196,1218]" name="Philippines" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Philippines</collectingCountry>
). One species, 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFCC6FB03FA24149F" authority="(CAMERON, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[795,1080,1196,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFCC6FB03FD6E149C" box="[795,882,1196,1217]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. niger</emphasis>
(CAMERON, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
, has been recorded from Assam and one, 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFDB3FB66FCD11483" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[622,717,1225,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFDB3FB66FCD11483" box="[622,717,1225,1246]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="E6EF764A9266FFEDFCC7FB66FD461482" box="[794,858,1225,1247]" name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">China</collectingCountry>
. The similar external characters suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFE74FB48FC4214A6" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[425,606,1254,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multimpressus">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFE74FB48FC4214A6" box="[425,606,1254,1276]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. multimpressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFCE8FB48FD8F14A6" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[821,915,1254,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFCE8FB48FD8F14A6" box="[821,915,1254,1276]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which too was desribed from 
<collectingRegion id="5C3CF8389266FFEDFE91FAABFF831544" box="[332,415,1284,1305]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
. It differs from this species by the coloration (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFC4DFAABFDF11545" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[912,1005,1283,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFC4DFAABFDF11545" box="[912,1005,1283,1305]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: lateral extensions of abdominal sternites III-V dark yellowish), the shorter antennae (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFC07FA8EFA2A156B" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[986,1078,1313,1334]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFC07FA8EFA2A156B" box="[986,1078,1313,1334]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: approximately 
<quantity id="59009B3F9266FFEDFE96FA91FF9A1509" box="[331,390,1342,1364]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long), the punctation of the head (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFD35FA91FD5E150E" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[744,834,1342,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFD35FA91FD5E150E" box="[744,834,1342,1363]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: postero-median portion of head without punctures), the less convex (cross-section) and more transverse pronotum (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFEF9FAD6FF6315D3" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[292,383,1401,1422]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFEF9FAD6FF6315D3" box="[292,383,1401,1422]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: approximately 1.2 times as broad as long), the finer punctation and different impressions on the pronotum (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFD97FA39FCB915F6" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[586,677,1430,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFD97FA39FCB915F6" box="[586,677,1430,1451]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: with two impressions on either side of middle and with long transverse impression near posterior margin), the shorter legs (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFBF9FA1BFEF115B8" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFBF9FA1BFEF115B8" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: metatibia approximately 
<quantity id="59009B3F9266FFEDFDDFFA7EFC5C15BB" box="[514,576,1489,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long), the shorter and differently shaped lateral extensions of the abdominal sternite III-V, the broader abdominal tergites (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFC70FA41FA1B165E" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[941,1031,1518,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFC70FA41FA1B165E" box="[941,1031,1518,1539]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: disc of tergite V barely 1.5 times as broad as long), and by the shape of the spermatheca. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599266FFEDFE8EF986FFAD1660" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[339,433,1576,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89266FFEDFE8EF986FFAD1660" box="[339,433,1576,1598]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="FA694B2B9266FFEDFE3BF987FC9F1663" author="ASSING V" box="[486,643,1576,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" pagination="1093 - 1104" refId="ref13195" refString="ASSING V. (2010): Two new species and additional records of Lomechusini from the Palaearctic region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 42 (2): 1093 - 1104." type="journal article" year="2010">ASSING (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. The new species is readily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599267FFECFF31FF74FF5E10AD" baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[236,322,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89267FFECFF31FF74FF5E10AD" box="[236,322,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">O. niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the darker antennae (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599267FFECFD95FF74FC8210AD" baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[584,670,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89267FFECFD95FF74FC8210AD" box="[584,670,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">O. niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: antennae yellowish-red with the apical three antennomeres black), the shapes of the lateral projections of the abdominal sternites III-VI (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599267FFECFEDDFEB9FF4B1176" baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[256,343,278,299]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89267FFECFEDDFEB9FF4B1176" box="[256,343,278,299]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">O. niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: lateral projections of sternite IV bifid), and the different shape of the abdominal tergite VIII (
<taxonomicName id="59F84D599267FFECFE73FE9CFC1A1115" baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[430,518,307,328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="AC8CEAC89267FFECFE73FE9CFC1A1115" box="[430,518,307,328]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">O. niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: posterior margin broadly and deeply emarginate, the middle of the emargination with a stout blunt tooth).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6E265519267FFECFF6FFEDAFDF811F5" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9E4736DA9267FFECFF6FFEDAFDF811F5" blockId="17.[178,1085,373,424]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
Distribution and natural history: The 
<typeStatus id="414388789267FFECFCEAFED9FD7F11D6" box="[823,867,374,395]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated in southwestern 
<collectingRegion id="5C3CF8389267FFECFEE3FE3CFF9211F5" box="[318,398,403,424]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
at an altitude of 
<quantity id="59009B3F9267FFECFDE4FE3CFC9411F5" box="[569,648,403,424]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
. Additional data are not available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
